WEBVTT

00:04.526 --> 00:04.700
.

00:04.743 --> 00:07.137
- In the nation's
largest city,

00:07.181 --> 00:09.879
the vicious and violent
members of the underworld

00:09.922 --> 00:11.489
are hunted by the detectives

00:11.533 --> 00:14.710
of the Organized Crime
Control Bureau.

00:14.753 --> 00:18.583
These are their stories.

00:18.627 --> 00:21.586
[pensive music]

00:21.630 --> 00:28.550
♪

00:36.123 --> 00:37.559
- I need your service weapon.

00:52.487 --> 00:54.706
- Do you own any other weapons?
- Glock 43.

00:54.750 --> 00:57.013
Drawer, nightstand
on the side of my bed.

00:57.057 --> 00:58.580
- Send a car to the residence.

01:00.538 --> 01:02.714
Detective Stabler,
you're being suspended

01:02.758 --> 01:05.500
pending an
internal investigation.

01:05.543 --> 01:07.980
You'll be notified of any
and all hearings

01:08.024 --> 01:09.852
as soon as they are scheduled.

01:09.895 --> 01:11.897
You are free to go.

01:11.941 --> 01:18.817
♪

01:18.861 --> 01:20.819
- That one's on me.
Frank Donnelly.

01:20.863 --> 01:23.083
- I remember you.
I remember your father.

01:23.126 --> 01:24.736
- Yeah, our dads,
they were like--

01:24.780 --> 01:26.738
- They were brothers.

01:26.782 --> 01:28.740
- You could use a brother
who's got your back

01:28.784 --> 01:30.133
right about now.

01:30.177 --> 01:37.271
♪

01:41.797 --> 01:43.538
- You're gonna
catch your death out here.

01:43.581 --> 01:44.365
- Donelly!

01:44.408 --> 01:46.367
Hey, what're you doing?

01:46.410 --> 01:48.151
- I swung by your house,
your kid said you were

01:48.195 --> 01:50.153
out here jogging,
trying to stay in shape.

01:50.197 --> 01:51.328
But I'm thinking,

01:51.372 --> 01:53.025
"Stay in shape for what?"
- [scoffs]

01:53.069 --> 01:55.158
- Not like he has
a job anymore.

01:55.202 --> 01:57.900
- Ah,
my suspension's temporary.

01:57.943 --> 01:59.597
- Says you.

01:59.641 --> 02:01.164
That Black chick
you used to work with,

02:01.208 --> 02:02.948
she says otherwise.

02:02.992 --> 02:05.037
- What does that mean?

02:05.081 --> 02:06.343
- Everybody's
got a podcast now,

02:06.387 --> 02:08.954
including the department.

02:08.998 --> 02:11.348
Sergeant Ayanna Bell.

02:11.392 --> 02:12.958
- Now, before we wrap this up,
Sergeant Bell,

02:13.002 --> 02:15.135
I want to ask you about
Detective Elliot Stabler.

02:15.178 --> 02:17.354
It's been three weeks
since he was suspended

02:17.398 --> 02:19.791
for his role in
the Richard Wheatley affair.

02:19.835 --> 02:22.142
Does he still have a future
with the department?

02:22.185 --> 02:25.188
- Detective Stabler's future
is out of my hands,

02:25.232 --> 02:26.972
but no one is above the law.

02:27.016 --> 02:28.191
- But wasn't Detective Stabler

02:28.235 --> 02:30.367
an indispensable member
of your team?

02:30.411 --> 02:32.978
- No one person
is indispensable.

02:33.022 --> 02:36.199
[tense music]

02:36.243 --> 02:38.636
- Personally?

02:38.680 --> 02:40.769
I'd go to war.

02:40.812 --> 02:45.469
♪

02:45.513 --> 02:48.342
- Okay, baby, I'll give you
a call after this meeting.

02:48.385 --> 02:51.171
Yeah, give--give Jack
a kiss for me.

02:51.214 --> 02:52.955
Okay, love you too.

02:52.998 --> 02:54.652
Hi, Sergeant Ayanna Bell.

02:54.696 --> 02:56.567
I'm here
for Lieutenant Brewster.

02:56.611 --> 02:59.309
- Thanks for throwing me
under the bus.

02:59.353 --> 03:00.789
- What are you doing here?

03:00.832 --> 03:02.443
- I'm looking for you.
You got a minute?

03:02.486 --> 03:04.749
- No.
- No?

03:04.793 --> 03:06.795
Ayanna, you throw me under
the bus and you walk away?

03:06.838 --> 03:09.363
I wanna talk to you.

03:09.406 --> 03:10.451
- I know you've been
on suspension

03:10.494 --> 03:11.669
for a while, Detective,

03:11.713 --> 03:13.193
so I think you forgot
how this works.

03:13.236 --> 03:14.498
Let me remind you.

03:14.542 --> 03:16.152
You will address me
as "Sergeant Bell."

03:16.196 --> 03:17.501
- Why'd you throw me
under the bus, Sergeant Bell?

03:17.545 --> 03:18.894
- And you can shout
all you want...

03:18.937 --> 03:20.069
- I'm not shouting.
- But if you think I'm gonna

03:20.112 --> 03:21.723
take the bait--
- I'm asking a question.

03:21.766 --> 03:23.072
- No person is indispensable,
what does that mean?

03:23.115 --> 03:25.509
- It was a fact. Deal with it.

03:25.553 --> 03:26.597
- You deal with this.

03:26.641 --> 03:28.033
You know something, in my day?

03:28.077 --> 03:29.209
Cops...

03:30.471 --> 03:32.124
They didn't throw other cops
under the bus.

03:32.168 --> 03:33.648
We had each other's back.

03:33.691 --> 03:34.866
Yeah, and you know something?

03:34.910 --> 03:36.781
if you ever become a cop
as long as I have,

03:36.825 --> 03:38.392
maybe you'll understand.

03:38.435 --> 03:39.697
If you last that long.
- You know what?

03:39.741 --> 03:40.785
It's true.

03:40.829 --> 03:42.526
You have been a cop
for a long time.

03:42.570 --> 03:44.920
Yet you work under me.

03:44.963 --> 03:46.443
So if we're keeping it a buck,
you need to consider...

03:46.487 --> 03:47.531
- Yeah, keep it a buck.
- What that says about you.

03:47.575 --> 03:50.621
- Sergeant, Detective.

03:50.665 --> 03:52.406
What the hell is going on here?

03:52.449 --> 03:54.234
- It's fine, this is nothing.

03:54.277 --> 03:55.974
- It doesn't
sound like nothing.

03:56.018 --> 03:58.934
- With all due respect,
Captain, it's been handled.

03:58.977 --> 04:00.979
I have a meeting upstairs.
Excuse me.

04:01.023 --> 04:02.198
- Hasn't been hand--

04:02.242 --> 04:03.243
all right, what--
what are you doing here?

04:03.286 --> 04:04.244
- I have a meeting too.

04:04.287 --> 04:05.723
- With McGrath?

04:05.767 --> 04:07.377
Can you talk to him
about my suspension?

04:07.421 --> 04:08.552
- Are you kidding me?

04:08.596 --> 04:09.901
What are you--
what are you doing?

04:09.945 --> 04:11.903
Having an outburst
in the middle of 1PP?

04:11.947 --> 04:14.297
I'm sure he's gonna find out
about it, and when he does,

04:14.341 --> 04:16.430
he's more likely
to extend your suspension.

04:16.473 --> 04:23.263
♪

04:24.133 --> 04:27.136
[tense music]

04:27.179 --> 04:34.274
♪

05:12.137 --> 05:14.183
[laughter]

05:14.226 --> 05:15.837
- One. All right.

05:15.880 --> 05:17.317
- Two.

05:17.360 --> 05:19.231
- Three!
- Go!

05:19.275 --> 05:20.363
- Carling.

05:20.407 --> 05:22.670
- Yeah.
- Yes.

05:22.713 --> 05:24.367
Uh...

05:24.411 --> 05:25.368
Bolton.
- Okay.

05:25.412 --> 05:28.153
- Yes.

05:28.197 --> 05:29.459
Ooh, I think he's stuck.

05:29.503 --> 05:31.287
- Stanwood.
- Oh!

05:31.331 --> 05:33.333
- Okay!
- Okay, okay!

05:33.376 --> 05:35.813
- Three left.

05:35.857 --> 05:37.772
He can't do it, he can't do it,
he can't do it.

05:37.815 --> 05:38.903
- Parnell.
- All right.

05:38.947 --> 05:42.080
- Oh!
- Down to two, final two.

05:42.124 --> 05:44.518
- And I wanna say...

05:44.561 --> 05:46.389
Santos and Yoshida,
but I don't wanna be

05:46.433 --> 05:50.350
accused of profiling, so I'm
gonna say Santos and Yoshida.

05:50.393 --> 05:51.351
[laughter]

05:51.394 --> 05:54.005
- Excuse me?

05:54.049 --> 05:55.877
- Apologies, Yoshida.
- What'd I tell you?

05:55.920 --> 05:57.357
This guy's
sharp as a freakin' tack.

05:57.400 --> 05:58.880
[glasses clinking]

05:58.923 --> 06:01.099
Right? It's Stabler.
- Nice.

06:01.143 --> 06:02.710
- Nice job, man.

06:02.753 --> 06:04.581
- It's a damn shame how the
department's treating you, man.

06:04.625 --> 06:06.540
You oughta be out there
chasing bad guys,

06:06.583 --> 06:08.585
not sitting at a desk
shuffling papers.

06:08.629 --> 06:10.021
- Thanks, man.

06:10.065 --> 06:11.414
And thanks for introducing me
to your friends.

06:11.458 --> 06:12.502
- Don't worry about it, man,
this is--

06:12.546 --> 06:13.503
we're cops, all right?

06:13.547 --> 06:15.026
We take care of each other.

06:15.070 --> 06:17.202
But this group, really,
we take care of each other.

06:17.246 --> 06:18.465
- That's right.
- Yeah.

06:18.508 --> 06:20.031
You can depend on us,
right guys?

06:20.075 --> 06:22.556
- Brotherhood.
- Here we go, Stabler!

06:22.599 --> 06:23.600
Oh, he's going
straight from the bottle.

06:23.644 --> 06:27.038
- Oh, no!
- Whoa!

06:27.082 --> 06:29.867
- I'm gonna guess that table
after these last two shots.

06:29.911 --> 06:33.131
[laughter]

06:33.175 --> 06:37.222
[tense music]

06:37.266 --> 06:38.223
- Hey.

06:38.267 --> 06:45.187
♪

06:51.062 --> 06:52.760
- Thank you so much
for your help, Captain.

06:52.803 --> 06:54.239
We could not have done that
without you.

06:54.283 --> 06:55.719
- No thanks necessary.

06:55.763 --> 06:59.549
This has to be a priority
for all of us.

06:59.593 --> 07:00.594
Where is he?

07:00.637 --> 07:06.904
♪

07:06.948 --> 07:07.949
Hey.

07:07.992 --> 07:10.473
- Hey.

07:10.517 --> 07:12.780
- That was uncomfortable.
- It really was.

07:12.823 --> 07:14.303
But there's nothing like
a screaming match

07:14.346 --> 07:16.697
in the middle of 1PP to get
the NYPD rumor mill going.

07:16.740 --> 07:18.916
- Did Donnelly buy it?

07:20.527 --> 07:22.833
- I'm willing to wager the
eight shots I just had with him

07:22.877 --> 07:25.401
at his cop bar
that he did, yeah.

07:25.445 --> 07:32.016
♪

07:32.669 --> 07:34.932
- So your UC was right
about Donnelly

07:34.976 --> 07:36.804
taking bribes
from the Marcy Killers.

07:36.847 --> 07:38.240
- Well, we've all heard
the stories

07:38.283 --> 07:39.763
of bad cops out of the 3-7,

07:39.807 --> 07:41.939
I just never thought
it'd be Donnelly.

07:41.983 --> 07:43.506
- You've known him
for a while, right?

07:43.550 --> 07:44.681
- Yeah, yeah.

07:44.725 --> 07:46.553
Our fathers were friends.

07:49.164 --> 07:50.992
- How are you doing
with all that?

07:52.950 --> 07:54.778
- My old man
would have hated this.

07:56.388 --> 07:58.260
"What are you doing,
go after the Marcy Killers,

07:58.303 --> 08:00.871
they're the bad guys,
leave your fellow cops alone."

08:00.915 --> 08:02.351
- Elliot,
that was a different time.

08:02.394 --> 08:03.787
That was your father.

08:03.831 --> 08:05.789
You had to go along
to get along.

08:07.530 --> 08:10.141
- He was a tough ass.

08:10.185 --> 08:12.056
Not perfect.

08:12.100 --> 08:13.101
But...

08:13.144 --> 08:14.755
[pensive music]

08:14.798 --> 08:16.713
He was a good cop.
- Elliot.

08:19.237 --> 08:20.238
My friend.

08:22.589 --> 08:24.025
You're doing the right thing.

08:27.419 --> 08:29.421
- Olivia, my friend,
can I take you and Noah

08:29.465 --> 08:31.206
out to lunch this weekend?

08:33.164 --> 08:35.123
- Let's wait, okay?

08:35.166 --> 08:37.908
Noah, you know,
he gets attached very easily,

08:37.952 --> 08:41.608
and you're undercover again.

08:43.087 --> 08:44.045
- Am I?

08:46.047 --> 08:47.222
- You are.

08:48.832 --> 08:50.878
You're undercover
as Elliot Stabler.

08:58.407 --> 09:00.931
[applause]

09:00.975 --> 09:03.020
- I'm not gonna
take up much time

09:03.064 --> 09:04.848
because today really
isn't about me,

09:04.892 --> 09:07.982
it's about each
and every one of you.

09:08.025 --> 09:10.811
I got a call
from my old friend,

09:10.854 --> 09:12.987
Congressman Leon Kilbride,

09:13.030 --> 09:15.859
informing me that
this school's students

09:15.903 --> 09:18.340
were in need
of a few computers.

09:18.383 --> 09:20.081
"A few?" I said.

09:20.124 --> 09:22.213
"Well, I think we can
do a little better than that."

09:22.257 --> 09:24.346
[applause]

09:24.389 --> 09:26.609
- What my friend, Mr. Webb,
is too modest to point out

09:26.653 --> 09:28.437
so I'll do it for him is that

09:28.480 --> 09:30.657
his commitment to this
community is so strong.

09:30.700 --> 09:33.747
Not only did he arrange for
the donation of new computers,

09:33.790 --> 09:35.487
but he is
personally bankrolling

09:35.531 --> 09:38.708
the construction of a whole
new computer lab for next year.

09:38.752 --> 09:41.058
Not bad for a couple
of homeboys who grew up

09:41.102 --> 09:43.017
not too far from here
over in Marcy, right?

09:43.060 --> 09:44.496
[chuckles]

09:44.540 --> 09:46.411
[cheers and applause]

09:46.455 --> 09:49.414
[tense music]

09:49.458 --> 09:50.677
♪

09:50.720 --> 09:54.071
[phone buzzing]

09:54.115 --> 09:55.116
- Hello?

09:57.161 --> 09:59.076
Mr. Webb?

09:59.120 --> 10:00.208
It's Hugo.

10:00.251 --> 10:01.688
He says he's been
trying to reach you.

10:01.731 --> 10:03.080
- I've been busy,
what does he want?

10:03.124 --> 10:05.561
- There's a little problem
at the warehouse.

10:05.605 --> 10:12.699
♪

10:25.712 --> 10:27.888
- Anything you wanna tell me,
Chopper?

10:33.502 --> 10:35.635
- No, sir.

10:35.678 --> 10:37.811
- Because I understand from
Hugo that you're thinking about

10:37.854 --> 10:40.640
leaving my organization
and starting your own.

10:40.683 --> 10:47.821
♪

10:49.344 --> 10:51.128
- I got my own connects.

10:51.172 --> 10:52.826
[all chuckle]

10:52.869 --> 10:54.654
- You know, there's something
you just might not

10:54.697 --> 10:57.482
be aware of, son.

10:57.526 --> 11:01.965
The Colombians
who dealt with the Albanians

11:02.009 --> 11:04.011
now deal exclusively...

11:05.534 --> 11:06.970
With me.

11:08.276 --> 11:11.366
So that connect that
you thought you had...

11:11.409 --> 11:16.719
♪

11:16.763 --> 11:22.290
I've outmaneuvered,
outplayed, outlasted

11:22.333 --> 11:24.335
all my rivals.

11:25.859 --> 11:27.730
Which means one thing...

11:29.645 --> 11:31.386
I run this town now.

11:37.392 --> 11:39.873
- Nova's undercover work
inside the Marcy Killers

11:39.916 --> 11:42.919
has led to a discovery
of a symbiotic relationship

11:42.963 --> 11:46.444
between the MKs
and Congressman Leon Kilbride.

11:46.488 --> 11:48.490
- The Textbooks and Toys guy?

11:48.533 --> 11:50.187
- That's not all he is. Read.

11:50.231 --> 11:52.233
- Bribery, racketeering,
money laundering,

11:52.276 --> 11:54.714
and various forms
of political corruption.

11:54.757 --> 11:56.193
- Crimes committed
under the cover

11:56.237 --> 11:59.588
of his status
as an elected official.

11:59.631 --> 12:01.372
Kilbride and Webb go way back.

12:01.416 --> 12:03.548
Webb has
several legitimate businesses,

12:03.592 --> 12:06.769
including a construction firm
that's received millions

12:06.813 --> 12:09.032
in government contracts
and PPP loans.

12:09.076 --> 12:10.294
- Looks like he got a job

12:10.338 --> 12:12.209
building Kilbride's
new library.

12:12.253 --> 12:13.297
- A chunk of the funds
are going

12:13.341 --> 12:14.995
straight into
Kilbride's pockets.

12:15.038 --> 12:15.996
I've seen it firsthand.

12:16.039 --> 12:17.606
- He's a hometown hero.

12:17.649 --> 12:19.260
People are not gonna love it
when we take him down.

12:19.303 --> 12:21.479
- Well,
we're not in the business

12:21.523 --> 12:23.873
of getting people to love us.

12:23.917 --> 12:25.483
Nova's reported that
Preston Webb

12:25.527 --> 12:28.051
has called his lieutenants
to a high-level meeting.

12:28.095 --> 12:30.662
Moldonado and Cho,
I want you outside

12:30.706 --> 12:31.881
surveilling the meeting.

12:31.925 --> 12:33.796
We're building a record
on them,

12:33.840 --> 12:35.929
both together and separately.

12:37.626 --> 12:39.933
- Sergeant, if we're all good
here, you mind if I bounce?

12:39.976 --> 12:42.022
- Is that Kilbride texting you?

12:42.065 --> 12:43.893
- Nah, it's family.

12:49.812 --> 12:52.859
- So we'll stage
the meet and greet here.

12:52.902 --> 12:55.383
High-level donors
each get a five-minute

12:55.426 --> 12:56.819
face to face with you,

12:56.863 --> 12:58.778
and I thought
we could do it right here,

12:58.821 --> 13:01.041
in front
of Don Ocura's effacement.

13:02.694 --> 13:03.913
What do you think?

13:03.957 --> 13:05.523
- Brilliant.
- [chuckles]

13:05.567 --> 13:07.438
- If you ever tire
of the art world, Cassandra,

13:07.482 --> 13:09.614
you'd make a superb
political rainmaker.

13:09.658 --> 13:10.877
- [chuckles]
Please.

13:10.920 --> 13:13.227
- As brilliant
as she is beautiful.

13:13.270 --> 13:16.230
That is why I married her.
[chuckles]

13:16.273 --> 13:18.101
As charming as he is trite.

13:18.145 --> 13:19.755
That is why
we're still married.

13:19.799 --> 13:21.539
[both chuckle]

13:21.583 --> 13:23.498
Got some calls,
I'll leave you to it.

13:26.849 --> 13:28.285
- Hmm.

13:28.329 --> 13:29.809
- I gather you took care
of that little problem

13:29.852 --> 13:31.158
at the warehouse.

13:31.201 --> 13:32.463
- Yeah, that was nothing.

13:32.507 --> 13:34.770
Just had to let Chopper know
what's what.

13:34.814 --> 13:38.687
- And you're confident there's
not a rising insurgency?

13:38.730 --> 13:41.864
- I called a summit
of my five vice presidents.

13:41.908 --> 13:45.912
A little restructuring will
keep the young bulls in line.

13:45.955 --> 13:49.045
[tense music]

13:51.395 --> 13:54.355
[somber music]

13:54.398 --> 14:01.318
♪

14:07.890 --> 14:09.370
- You didn't pray?

14:12.460 --> 14:14.157
Okay.

14:16.333 --> 14:19.380
Look, I know church isn't
really your thing,

14:19.423 --> 14:20.816
but it would mean a lot to me
if you were there

14:20.860 --> 14:22.557
to support me on Sunday.

14:22.600 --> 14:24.907
- I wouldn't miss it
for the world, D.

14:24.951 --> 14:26.996
- Good.

14:27.040 --> 14:28.563
Now let's go eat.

14:32.567 --> 14:34.351
- Bye, Mom and Dad.

14:34.395 --> 14:35.352
I love you.

14:35.396 --> 14:42.316
♪

14:46.015 --> 14:46.189
.

14:46.233 --> 14:48.888
- What an incredible
performance from...

14:48.931 --> 14:50.977
- Aw, man,
this guy is unbelievable.

14:51.020 --> 14:52.761
I mean, he's supposed to be out

14:52.804 --> 14:53.936
the whole season
with a knee injury.

14:53.980 --> 14:56.286
He just hit
an unbelievable jump shot.

14:56.330 --> 14:57.374
[phone ringing]

14:57.418 --> 14:58.985
- Hello?

14:59.028 --> 15:01.813
Hey, uh, now's not a good time.

15:01.857 --> 15:03.903
Can you call me back next week?

15:03.946 --> 15:05.600
Yeah, I know I'm past due,

15:05.643 --> 15:08.168
but, uh, now's just not
a good time, so...

15:09.517 --> 15:10.910
[sighs]
I understand,

15:10.953 --> 15:12.824
but like I said,
just call me back, all right?

15:12.868 --> 15:14.217
Thank you, have a nice day.

15:14.261 --> 15:15.697
[phone beeps]

15:18.526 --> 15:20.310
[sighs]

15:20.354 --> 15:21.616
- Everything all right?

15:21.659 --> 15:23.400
- My kid's school.

15:23.444 --> 15:26.969
They've got a bug up their ass
about tuition or whatever.

15:27.013 --> 15:28.492
- Yeah.

15:28.536 --> 15:29.493
[phone ringing]

15:29.537 --> 15:31.626
Vultures, man. Just vultures.

15:34.020 --> 15:35.543
- Ain't none of my business,
but...

15:37.284 --> 15:38.589
We're gonna sit here
and try to watch the game,

15:38.633 --> 15:39.721
they're just gonna
keep calling.

15:39.764 --> 15:41.853
- Let 'em keep calling.
- You know?

15:41.897 --> 15:43.159
- What do you want me to do,
unplug the thing?

15:43.203 --> 15:44.639
- [chuckles]

15:46.380 --> 15:49.296
- Tell you what.

15:49.339 --> 15:50.645
Let's go to my place.

15:52.777 --> 15:54.127
I got something
I wanna show you anyways.

15:55.780 --> 15:57.260
- Don't need to ask me twice,
man, let's go.

15:57.304 --> 16:00.524
[phone ringing]

16:00.568 --> 16:03.266
[tense music]

16:03.310 --> 16:07.009
[line trilling]

16:07.053 --> 16:08.054
- No answer.

16:08.097 --> 16:09.577
Guessing it worked.
- [chuckles]

16:09.620 --> 16:12.667
- Nothing unites people
like annoying bill collectors.

16:12.710 --> 16:14.582
[cheerful music]

16:14.625 --> 16:19.195
[gospel choir vocalizing]

16:26.681 --> 16:27.856
- Good morning.

16:30.076 --> 16:32.861
- Good morning,
Ezekiel Baptist.

16:32.904 --> 16:35.777
all: Good morning,
Pastor Riley.

16:35.820 --> 16:37.779
- So I want to talk
to you today...

16:39.389 --> 16:41.826
About love.

16:41.870 --> 16:44.133
In the book of Luke,
Jesus tells us

16:44.177 --> 16:47.919
to love the Lord
with all our hearts.

16:47.963 --> 16:49.269
- That's true.
- It does.

16:49.312 --> 16:53.795
- And to love our neighbor
as ourselves.

16:53.838 --> 16:55.579
- Yes.
- That's right.

16:55.623 --> 16:57.581
- Over time,

16:57.625 --> 17:01.629
love thy neighbor became

17:01.672 --> 17:03.935
every man for himself

17:03.979 --> 17:07.939
and little by little,
day by day,

17:07.983 --> 17:11.291
that's how
a sense of community gets lost.

17:11.334 --> 17:16.383
A breakdown in community
creates a void,

17:16.426 --> 17:18.341
and then what happens?

17:18.385 --> 17:21.257
Then what happens, beloved?

17:21.301 --> 17:26.697
Drugs and crime enter
to fill that void.

17:26.741 --> 17:28.308
- Wonderful sermon,
young brother.

17:28.351 --> 17:30.440
- Thank you, sir.
- Yeah, Preston Webb.

17:30.484 --> 17:31.528
My wife, Cassandra.

17:31.572 --> 17:32.790
- It was so inspiring.

17:32.834 --> 17:34.401
You really have a gift.

17:34.444 --> 17:37.230
I just hope I impressed
my little sister.

17:37.273 --> 17:40.233
[tense music]

17:40.276 --> 17:41.408
♪

17:41.451 --> 17:42.844
- Oh, Carmen is your sister?

17:42.887 --> 17:45.238
I had no idea.

17:45.281 --> 17:47.718
Yeah, you're full of surprises,
young lady.

17:47.762 --> 17:49.155
- She sure is.

17:55.509 --> 17:56.423
- Here you go, pal.

17:58.860 --> 18:02.342
5:00 somewhere, right?

18:02.385 --> 18:03.386
- Right.

18:05.214 --> 18:06.389
- [sighs]

18:08.304 --> 18:10.132
- Five kids?

18:10.176 --> 18:11.002
Same.

18:11.046 --> 18:13.788
- Yeah, soon to be six.

18:13.831 --> 18:16.660
Yeah, those five are all
from my, uh, first wife

18:16.704 --> 18:18.749
and got another on the way

18:18.793 --> 18:20.795
with wife number two.

18:20.838 --> 18:23.711
- Well, here's to stayin' busy.

18:23.754 --> 18:25.016
- Yeah.

18:25.060 --> 18:27.628
Busy writing checks.

18:27.671 --> 18:32.589
Alimony, child support,
getting ready for the new one.

18:32.633 --> 18:34.722
The struggle is real,
my friend.

18:36.289 --> 18:37.290
But...

18:38.682 --> 18:40.467
It's not all bad.

18:40.510 --> 18:42.643
Come here,
I wanna show you something.

18:42.686 --> 18:43.905
Come on.

18:47.778 --> 18:50.041
Eh?

18:50.085 --> 18:52.174
- That's beautiful.

18:52.218 --> 18:56.047
- Yep.
It's my one guilty pleasure.

18:56.091 --> 18:57.397
Come on, take her for a spin.

18:57.440 --> 19:01.314
[upbeat rock music]

19:01.357 --> 19:03.272
You know,
it's not like--I don't

19:03.316 --> 19:05.318
drive into work
with this thing, you know?

19:05.361 --> 19:07.189
Guy on my salary pulls up
to the precinct

19:07.233 --> 19:08.886
with a beauty like this,
believe me,

19:08.930 --> 19:11.367
that would raise, uh,
a lot of questions.

19:11.411 --> 19:13.761
- Everybody's looking to pinch
us with something these days.

19:13.804 --> 19:15.719
- Oh, yeah, man, it's crazy.

19:15.763 --> 19:17.025
The whole world hates cops now.

19:17.068 --> 19:18.635
You know why?
- [sighs]

19:18.679 --> 19:21.116
- Cell phones. Yeah.

19:21.160 --> 19:23.553
You could do a hundred things
right in the course of a day.

19:23.597 --> 19:25.338
You make one wrong move?

19:25.381 --> 19:27.992
Bam, it's on video,
then it's on the internet.

19:28.036 --> 19:29.864
Next thing you know,
it's all over social media,

19:29.907 --> 19:31.996
your career's over,
your life's over.

19:32.040 --> 19:33.259
You know?
[phone ringing]

19:33.302 --> 19:35.435
Oh, hang on.

19:35.478 --> 19:36.436
Yeah?

19:38.438 --> 19:39.352
What?

19:41.267 --> 19:42.877
No, no, I can't do that now.

19:46.446 --> 19:49.013
All right, all right, relax,
I'll be right there.

19:52.278 --> 19:53.192
Listen.

19:55.629 --> 19:58.849
My dad always spoke very highly
of your dad, Stabler.

19:58.893 --> 20:00.547
He liked him.

20:00.590 --> 20:04.812
Hope the apple didn't fall far
from the tree, my friend.

20:04.855 --> 20:07.031
[engine revving]

20:07.075 --> 20:08.859
[tires screech]

20:10.644 --> 20:13.603
[tense music]

20:13.647 --> 20:20.523
♪

20:23.047 --> 20:24.788
- Sit tight.

20:24.832 --> 20:26.007
[grunts]

20:48.812 --> 20:50.379
- Yo, it's me.

20:50.423 --> 20:51.380
- Back here.

20:51.424 --> 20:58.344
♪

20:59.519 --> 21:00.868
- Oh, Jesus.

21:03.262 --> 21:04.654
- Looks like
a drug deal gone bad.

21:04.698 --> 21:06.874
Neighbors heard shots and
fired a couple of their own,

21:06.917 --> 21:08.963
scared off the perps.

21:09.006 --> 21:11.008
They left cash, drugs.

21:11.052 --> 21:12.706
We hit the jackpot
on this one, man.

21:12.749 --> 21:14.055
- Can't get greedy, okay?

21:14.098 --> 21:16.797
Leave the drugs so nobody
asks any questions.

21:16.840 --> 21:22.846
♪

21:22.890 --> 21:25.327
Told you to wait in the car.

21:25.371 --> 21:26.894
- Thought you might
need backup.

21:32.378 --> 21:33.335
- [sighs]

21:39.733 --> 21:40.951
- Cool with that?

21:46.043 --> 21:47.131
- Be a lot cooler with two.

21:47.175 --> 21:54.313
♪

21:59.840 --> 22:00.014
.

22:00.057 --> 22:02.364
- They just walked in
and robbed a crime scene

22:02.408 --> 22:03.713
in broad daylight?

22:03.757 --> 22:05.106
- Responding officer
tipped off Donnelly,

22:05.149 --> 22:07.674
they lifted the cash
before backup arrived.

22:07.717 --> 22:10.416
They were cool, casual,
they were disciplined.

22:10.459 --> 22:12.200
So this is not the first time
they've done this.

22:12.243 --> 22:13.854
- [scoffs]
It's the perfect crime.

22:13.897 --> 22:15.682
No way to nail 'em
for stolen drug money

22:15.725 --> 22:16.813
if it was never
logged into evidence.

22:16.857 --> 22:17.901
- And the big news is,

22:17.945 --> 22:19.294
these two
are not working alone.

22:19.338 --> 22:21.296
I think Donnelly's running
a crew out of the 3-7.

22:21.340 --> 22:22.384
- You think it's the ones

22:22.428 --> 22:23.646
he introduced you to
the other night?

22:23.690 --> 22:25.039
- I think
they're the core group.

22:25.082 --> 22:26.954
- You get their names?
- Uh.

22:26.997 --> 22:31.698
Carling, Bolton, Stanwood,
Yoshida, Santos, and Parnell.

22:31.741 --> 22:33.656
Parnell being the guy
who tipped off Donnelly.

22:33.700 --> 22:35.832
[tense music]

22:35.876 --> 22:37.399
- Are you sure
they were police?

22:37.443 --> 22:38.879
- No question.

22:38.922 --> 22:40.750
One went in,
a few minutes later,

22:40.794 --> 22:43.666
two more January 6-looking
dudes showed up.

22:43.710 --> 22:45.929
Then they come running out
with Mellow's bag.

22:45.973 --> 22:49.063
Next thing I know, the whole
block's a crime scene.

22:49.106 --> 22:51.065
- Thank you, Flip.

22:51.108 --> 22:54.503
♪

22:54.547 --> 22:56.679
- How much did we lose?

22:56.723 --> 22:58.899
- Mellow was holding
at least 50k.

23:00.379 --> 23:02.729
- It's a minor loss,
but the disrespect...

23:04.252 --> 23:07.560
Eh, that can't stand.

23:10.563 --> 23:12.260
Somebody's gotta pay.

23:14.131 --> 23:16.395
- Stabler's gotta get
back out on the street

23:16.438 --> 23:17.439
so let's do this fast.

23:17.483 --> 23:18.701
What do we have?

23:18.745 --> 23:20.660
- Not much on Parnell,
he's pretty clean.

23:20.703 --> 23:22.444
- Same for Bolton,
Carling, and the others.

23:22.488 --> 23:23.793
I'm seeing a few awards

23:23.837 --> 23:25.882
and a bunch of citations
here and there.

23:25.926 --> 23:28.058
- Donnelly's got a commendation
for placing himself

23:28.102 --> 23:30.104
in grave personal danger
in the line of duty.

23:30.147 --> 23:31.888
- That doesn't surprise me,
he was a good cop.

23:31.932 --> 23:33.368
- Yeah, unfortunately,

23:33.412 --> 23:36.197
he's also cheating on
his pregnant wife.

23:36.240 --> 23:37.720
- Where'd you find that?

23:37.764 --> 23:40.897
- You're in his official
personnel file, I'm in his DMs.

23:40.941 --> 23:42.812
We are not the same.

23:45.946 --> 23:48.035
- Stop--that's his crew.

23:48.078 --> 23:50.864
Donnelly's arm,
can you blow it up?

23:53.127 --> 23:55.956
I've seen that tattoo
somewhere before.

23:55.999 --> 23:58.219
- Hang on, let's see.

24:01.788 --> 24:03.354
- A ten and a three.

24:03.398 --> 24:05.052
- Damn, they all have it.

24:07.228 --> 24:08.359
- NYPD radio code.

24:08.403 --> 24:09.752
- To stop transmitting.

24:09.796 --> 24:11.362
- They have a code of silence.

24:11.406 --> 24:13.408
- Donnelly's more than
an errand boy

24:13.452 --> 24:14.888
for the Marcy Killers,

24:14.931 --> 24:18.587
he's the leader of a gang
operating inside the NYPD.

24:18.631 --> 24:25.812
♪

24:27.422 --> 24:29.642
- Preston Webb,
Hugo Bankole, and Nova

24:29.685 --> 24:31.078
just arrived at the location.

24:35.648 --> 24:36.997
- Welcome...

24:38.912 --> 24:40.653
To the dawn
of a new era, gentlemen.

24:40.696 --> 24:43.525
[chuckles]

24:43.569 --> 24:45.222
The Albanians are gone.

24:46.833 --> 24:48.356
So are the Italians.

24:49.966 --> 24:54.710
Both groups were felled
by hubris,

24:54.754 --> 24:59.498
greed, and infighting.

24:59.541 --> 25:01.848
But...

25:01.891 --> 25:03.414
There's a lesson...

25:03.458 --> 25:04.633
[wine pouring]

25:04.677 --> 25:06.461
In their failure.

25:08.463 --> 25:10.030
An opportunity.

25:15.426 --> 25:16.863
Ah...

25:19.213 --> 25:22.651
The Marcy Killers were formed
when two rival gangs

25:22.695 --> 25:25.045
merged back in the day.

25:25.088 --> 25:28.744
Now, over the years,
I've elevated a number of you

25:28.788 --> 25:31.355
and named you
as vice presidents.

25:31.399 --> 25:33.836
And I've encouraged
my vice presidents

25:33.880 --> 25:36.273
to operate autonomously

25:36.317 --> 25:38.841
because the decentralized
structure benefited us

25:38.885 --> 25:40.713
when our enemies were many.

25:40.756 --> 25:45.326
But it also led
to the proliferation

25:45.369 --> 25:47.023
of different factions,

25:47.067 --> 25:50.026
some of which seem to believe

25:50.070 --> 25:53.290
that their individual interests
are more important

25:53.334 --> 25:55.031
than the interests
of the whole.

25:57.033 --> 25:59.558
It's time for me
to rein you in.

25:59.601 --> 26:01.081
Effective immediately,

26:01.124 --> 26:04.040
I am consolidating
our current structure.

26:05.825 --> 26:09.524
Nova will no longer
be a vice president.

26:09.568 --> 26:13.136
- [chuckles]
Good.

26:13.180 --> 26:15.922
- Instead, she will now

26:15.965 --> 26:18.098
report directly to me,

26:18.141 --> 26:22.798
which means each of you will
now report directly to her.

26:22.842 --> 26:26.236
- Hold up, you think I'm gonna
take orders from this bitch?

26:26.280 --> 26:28.630
- Sit down, son.

26:28.674 --> 26:30.632
- No, I ain't sitting down.

26:30.676 --> 26:32.068
This is some bull.

26:32.112 --> 26:33.200
Look, Webb,
I've been rocking with you

26:33.243 --> 26:34.201
way longer than this chick,
man.

26:34.244 --> 26:35.419
You think I'm just gonna--

26:35.463 --> 26:37.596
[silverware clattering]

26:37.639 --> 26:39.859
[screams]

26:42.513 --> 26:44.428
[whimpering]

26:44.472 --> 26:46.082
- That's your second strike,
Chopper.

26:46.126 --> 26:47.344
There ain't gonna be a third.

26:47.388 --> 26:48.824
- [screams]

26:51.827 --> 26:52.001
.

26:52.045 --> 26:53.612
- Second in command?

26:53.655 --> 26:56.440
Of the entire Marcy
organization?

26:56.484 --> 26:58.051
Nova, I don't like this.

26:58.094 --> 26:59.661
I don't like it.

26:59.705 --> 27:01.837
This is more than what
you signed up for.

27:01.881 --> 27:05.406
- Trust me, you want
eyes and ears on the inside.

27:05.449 --> 27:07.016
And, respectfully,

27:07.060 --> 27:09.584
I didn't come this far
for you to make me quit.

27:09.628 --> 27:11.281
Here.

27:11.325 --> 27:14.371
[apprehensive music]

27:14.415 --> 27:17.113
- [sighs]

27:17.157 --> 27:19.159
- Who's Derek, and why
do I have his phone number?

27:20.726 --> 27:22.684
- Derek's my brother.

27:22.728 --> 27:24.512
He's a pastor
at Ezekiel Baptist.

27:24.555 --> 27:26.383
- You never
mentioned him before.

27:26.427 --> 27:28.298
- He doesn't know I'm a cop.

27:28.342 --> 27:30.213
He just thinks I'm mixed in
with a bad crowd.

27:32.041 --> 27:33.782
When this operation is over,
I plan to tell him.

27:33.826 --> 27:35.218
If you really
don't want me to do it?

27:35.262 --> 27:36.567
Call him, out me.

27:36.611 --> 27:42.922
♪

27:42.965 --> 27:44.706
Look, I know
you're just worried about

27:44.750 --> 27:47.666
losing another undercover,
and I appreciate it,

27:47.709 --> 27:49.015
but with all due respect,

27:49.058 --> 27:52.192
I've been swimming
in these waters for years.

27:52.235 --> 27:54.194
I know what I'm doing.

27:54.237 --> 27:55.978
You have to trust me.

27:58.981 --> 28:00.548
- [sighs]

28:00.591 --> 28:01.680
Fine.

28:03.246 --> 28:04.900
But watch your back.

28:07.424 --> 28:08.687
- See you at the fundraiser.

28:15.737 --> 28:16.956
- I'm here, did I miss it?

28:16.999 --> 28:19.262
- No, baby,
you're just in time.

28:21.612 --> 28:23.179
Preston...

28:23.223 --> 28:24.964
- Ah, that's nothing.

28:25.007 --> 28:27.096
Chopper just
got a little bit out of pocket.

28:27.140 --> 28:28.619
- [sighs]

28:28.663 --> 28:32.145
I told you to get rid of his
crazy ass a long time ago.

28:32.188 --> 28:37.498
Well, you can tell Chopper
the next time he ruins

28:37.541 --> 28:41.763
one of my husband's
$1,500 shirts,

28:41.807 --> 28:44.940
I'm gonna be the one
wearing his blood.

28:44.984 --> 28:47.334
- It's a boy.
- [gasps]

28:47.377 --> 28:49.249
Ah!
- [chuckles]

28:49.292 --> 28:50.946
[clapping]

28:50.990 --> 28:52.992
[sentimental music]

28:53.035 --> 28:55.037
- Come hold your grandson, Dad.

28:55.081 --> 28:56.212
- Aww.

29:01.740 --> 29:02.958
- Do we have a name?

29:03.002 --> 29:05.308
- Isaiah Preston Henderson Jr.

29:07.615 --> 29:11.053
- He's beautiful.

29:11.097 --> 29:13.055
Y'all did some damn good work.

29:16.319 --> 29:19.235
[phone ringing]

29:21.107 --> 29:22.064
- Yeah.

29:29.855 --> 29:31.421
Thanks, Hugo.

29:31.465 --> 29:33.989
Nice work.

29:34.033 --> 29:36.905
- All right,
here comes my client.

29:36.949 --> 29:37.993
- So how much
does this police chauffeur

29:38.037 --> 29:39.516
service of yours bring in?

29:39.560 --> 29:42.911
- Blue Line'll cost you
5,000 in cash, no exceptions.

29:42.955 --> 29:44.608
- Uh-huh.
- And you get driven around

29:44.652 --> 29:45.914
anywhere in the city,

29:45.958 --> 29:47.307
no legal entanglements.

29:49.004 --> 29:50.832
- Thanks for cutting me in.

29:50.876 --> 29:52.355
- We all got bills to pay,
right?

29:52.399 --> 29:53.792
There he is.

29:55.445 --> 29:56.707
What's up, Big Smoke?

29:56.751 --> 29:58.361
- Donnelly, what's good, baby?

29:58.405 --> 30:00.015
- Smoke, this is Stabler,
Stabler, this is Smoke.

30:00.059 --> 30:00.973
He's new.

30:01.016 --> 30:02.235
- Hey, man.
- What's up, man?

30:02.278 --> 30:03.758
Any friend of Donnelly's
is a friend of mine.

30:03.802 --> 30:04.977
Yo, let's hit it.

30:05.020 --> 30:08.371
[upbeat rock music]

30:08.415 --> 30:09.720
- Hey, yo, how's your lady?

30:09.764 --> 30:10.939
- Uh, thanks for asking, man.

30:10.983 --> 30:12.332
She's, uh, she's good.

30:12.375 --> 30:13.942
She's big as a house

30:13.986 --> 30:16.031
and probably gonna pop
any day now.

30:16.075 --> 30:17.859
- I tell you what,
get me to Harlem

30:17.903 --> 30:19.861
without getting
pulled over by the police,

30:19.905 --> 30:21.602
I'll let you name the kid
after me.

30:21.645 --> 30:23.169
[laughter]

30:23.212 --> 30:24.431
- Hey, screw you.

30:24.474 --> 30:26.607
- Ooh, baby,
that's what I'm talkin' about.

30:26.650 --> 30:28.914
- We don't call it taking the
Blue Line for nothing, boys.

30:31.307 --> 30:33.135
- Hey, yo,
you don't talk a lot, huh?

30:33.179 --> 30:36.922
- No, he's, uh,
he's just the money guy.

30:36.965 --> 30:39.663
- Oh, right, my bad.

30:39.707 --> 30:41.491
- Yeah.

30:41.535 --> 30:43.319
- ♪ It's bad business

30:43.363 --> 30:45.147
♪

30:45.191 --> 30:48.585
♪ It's bad business

30:48.629 --> 30:50.805
- There we go.
- All right.

30:51.806 --> 30:53.634
- All right, man.

30:53.677 --> 30:55.070
Hey, yo, I'll text you
when I'm ready to head back.

30:55.114 --> 30:57.377
- Okay.
- All right, couple hours.

31:00.728 --> 31:02.817
- Congrats, pal.
- Hmm?

31:02.861 --> 31:04.906
- You just busted
your Blue Line cherry.

31:04.950 --> 31:07.169
[engine turns over]

31:09.389 --> 31:10.869
- What the hell?

31:10.912 --> 31:12.218
- Sit tight.

31:12.261 --> 31:15.221
[tense music]

31:15.264 --> 31:16.526
♪

31:16.570 --> 31:18.964
Preston.

31:19.007 --> 31:21.923
- Seems there was an, uh,
unfortunate altercation

31:21.967 --> 31:24.883
inside one of my stash houses.

31:24.926 --> 31:27.929
Ended with two bodies
in the morgue,

31:27.973 --> 31:30.932
50 bands in the wind.

31:30.976 --> 31:32.760
You know anything about that?

31:32.803 --> 31:35.197
- You think I killed you guys?

31:35.241 --> 31:37.721
- I think one of your men
took my cash.

31:37.765 --> 31:39.680
- I have
too much respect for you

31:39.723 --> 31:41.900
for something
like that to happen.

31:41.943 --> 31:43.249
- Yeah, well, I hope,
for your sake,

31:43.292 --> 31:44.728
you're telling the truth,
Donnelly,

31:44.772 --> 31:46.817
because if you're not,

31:46.861 --> 31:51.735
that long standing alliance
between the Marcy organization

31:51.779 --> 31:52.823
and the Brotherhood?

31:52.867 --> 31:53.955
That's over.

31:57.263 --> 32:00.440
I swear on everything
I hold dear,

32:00.483 --> 32:02.268
blood will have blood.

32:02.311 --> 32:09.057
♪

32:14.976 --> 32:16.282
- Brotherhood?

32:27.119 --> 32:27.510
.

32:27.554 --> 32:29.686
- So what's the Brotherhood?

32:29.730 --> 32:31.297
- [sighs]

32:33.342 --> 32:36.084
We look after each other,
you know?

32:36.128 --> 32:38.260
Got each other's backs.

32:38.304 --> 32:41.481
And if the opportunity
to supplement

32:41.524 --> 32:44.919
our income presents itself,

32:44.963 --> 32:46.486
sometimes we take it.

32:46.529 --> 32:49.968
It's basically an extension
of what we do as cops.

32:50.011 --> 32:52.492
- Pretty liberal
interpretation of what cops do.

32:56.061 --> 32:57.540
- Are we gonna have
a problem here?

32:57.584 --> 32:58.672
- No, I just want
to make sure that

32:58.715 --> 33:00.195
I'm understanding
what this thing is.

33:00.239 --> 33:02.110
- I just told you what it is.
- 'Cause it seems like...

33:02.154 --> 33:04.199
[tense music]

33:04.243 --> 33:06.549
You're a gang.

33:09.291 --> 33:11.250
- That ain't--
that ain't what it is.

33:11.293 --> 33:12.468
No.

33:18.648 --> 33:21.477
[indistinct chatter]

33:21.521 --> 33:24.828
[soft upbeat music playing]

33:24.872 --> 33:26.352
- Oh, my God.

33:28.832 --> 33:31.226
- Hey, Ayanna! Excuse me.
Hey, what's up?

33:31.270 --> 33:32.793
- Oh.

33:32.836 --> 33:34.534
Hi, Carmen,
nice to see you again.

33:34.577 --> 33:36.014
I don't think you've
met my wife, Denise.

33:36.057 --> 33:37.319
- It's a pleasure
to meet you, Denise.

33:37.363 --> 33:38.625
- Pleasure.

33:38.668 --> 33:40.366
- Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen,

33:40.409 --> 33:42.107
and welcome.

33:42.150 --> 33:43.630
My name is Cassandra Webb,

33:43.673 --> 33:46.154
and as you may have guessed,
this is my gallery.

33:46.198 --> 33:47.590
[applause]

33:47.634 --> 33:50.811
- I think maybe
Kilbride's aide is family.

33:50.854 --> 33:52.030
- You think?
- [chuckles]

33:52.073 --> 33:53.944
- But I am here tonight

33:53.988 --> 33:57.470
as a longtime supporter
of my dear friend,

33:57.513 --> 33:59.733
Congressman Leon Kilbride.

33:59.776 --> 34:01.735
[applause]

34:01.778 --> 34:05.956
He's one of our most
tireless and dedicated,

34:06.000 --> 34:09.003
honest and passionate
representatives

34:09.047 --> 34:10.309
in Washington, D.C.

34:10.352 --> 34:12.441
[applause]

34:12.485 --> 34:14.095
[inaudible]

34:14.139 --> 34:15.357
- No, you don't--no.

34:15.401 --> 34:18.143
[laughter]

34:18.186 --> 34:19.970
Oh, oh.

34:20.014 --> 34:22.103
Ladies and gentlemen,

34:22.147 --> 34:25.237
my incorrigible husband
would like to say a few words.

34:25.280 --> 34:27.848
[laughter and applause]

34:31.765 --> 34:34.028
- Well, uh, listen, people,

34:34.072 --> 34:37.249
my wife is far too classy
to hit you with the hard sell.

34:37.292 --> 34:38.598
[laughter]

34:38.641 --> 34:40.556
But I'll do it.

34:40.600 --> 34:43.864
Now, everyone here knows
that campaigns cost money.

34:43.907 --> 34:46.040
National campaigns
cost a fortune.

34:46.084 --> 34:47.824
- Well, well, well.

34:47.868 --> 34:49.696
You're late, jackass.
[door slams]

34:49.739 --> 34:50.871
And you just put a target
on the back

34:50.914 --> 34:52.438
of every single cop
in this room.

34:52.481 --> 34:54.831
- Donnelly, take it easy, man--
- Take it easy, my ass.

34:54.875 --> 34:56.050
That was Preston Webb's money.

34:56.094 --> 34:58.096
Even a moron knows
you don't steal

34:58.139 --> 34:59.575
directly from Preston Webb.

34:59.619 --> 35:01.099
- I didn't know it was
Webb's stash house.

35:01.142 --> 35:02.187
- Ah, you didn't know.

35:02.230 --> 35:03.884
Oh, well,
then all is forgiven, huh?

35:03.927 --> 35:05.538
You're a cop,
it's your job to know!

35:05.581 --> 35:07.148
- Look,
can't he just apologize?

35:07.192 --> 35:09.542
Say they hit the wrong house?
It was a mix up.

35:09.585 --> 35:11.370
- Apologize to that
scumbag dealer?

35:11.413 --> 35:12.719
No way.

35:12.762 --> 35:14.547
- What do you propose we do,
Parnell, huh?

35:14.590 --> 35:17.158
- I propose
those Marcy Killers

35:17.202 --> 35:18.333
kiss my white ass.

35:18.377 --> 35:19.987
What are they gonna do,
call the cops?

35:20.030 --> 35:21.728
- Just unbelievable.

35:21.771 --> 35:23.860
You saw Webb,
he was out for blood.

35:23.904 --> 35:24.861
- Mm-hmm.

35:26.646 --> 35:28.082
- What do you think
we should do?

35:28.126 --> 35:29.170
- [sighs]

35:29.214 --> 35:30.650
You already told him
it wasn't us,

35:30.693 --> 35:31.825
so he's never gonna believe
it was an accident.

35:31.868 --> 35:34.219
- Why do we care--
- Shut up!

35:34.262 --> 35:35.698
Just shut up.

35:35.742 --> 35:38.701
[tense music]

35:38.745 --> 35:40.834
- So I think...

35:43.793 --> 35:46.056
We should just enjoy the cash.

35:48.189 --> 35:51.584
[all chuckling]

35:51.627 --> 35:53.194
- Hey, Donnelly,

35:53.238 --> 35:56.066
sounds like your guy's got
bigger balls than you.

35:56.110 --> 35:57.938
all:
Ooh!

35:57.981 --> 36:00.549
[laughter]

36:04.727 --> 36:06.207
[indistinct chatter]

36:06.251 --> 36:07.948
- My friends.

36:07.991 --> 36:10.124
I want you to meet
two of my favorite people,

36:10.168 --> 36:13.214
Denise Bullock and her wife,
Sergeant Ayanna Bell,

36:13.258 --> 36:15.085
Preston and Cassandra Webb.

36:15.129 --> 36:16.304
- Nice to meet you.

36:16.348 --> 36:18.176
- Your gallery is so...

36:19.655 --> 36:21.788
Wow.
- Thank you, Denise.

36:21.831 --> 36:23.093
- Thank you, Denise.

36:23.137 --> 36:25.444
[laughter]

36:25.487 --> 36:27.446
- Well, Sergeant Bell,

36:27.489 --> 36:29.970
I've been hearing all about you
and your remarkable career.

36:30.013 --> 36:32.625
Leon tells me that
you're headed for great things.

36:32.668 --> 36:34.366
- Oh, well,
that's very flattering.

36:34.409 --> 36:36.019
I have no idea what
he's talking about, though.

36:36.063 --> 36:37.673
- She's being modest,
trust me, you're looking

36:37.717 --> 36:39.284
at a future
police commissioner.

36:39.327 --> 36:41.590
- Hmm, well, the mayor's
around here somewhere,

36:41.634 --> 36:42.809
maybe we should just corner him

36:42.852 --> 36:44.463
and get you
on the shortlist early.

36:44.506 --> 36:46.378
- Sorry to interrupt.

36:46.421 --> 36:47.596
Mr. Webb,
there's a messenger here

36:47.640 --> 36:49.119
with something
that needs your signature.

36:49.163 --> 36:50.512
- Of course.

36:50.556 --> 36:52.645
Work never ends.

36:52.688 --> 36:54.168
- [chuckles]

36:54.212 --> 36:55.691
- Please, excuse me.

36:55.735 --> 36:59.304
♪

36:59.347 --> 37:01.784
- Yeah, it was Donnelly.

37:01.828 --> 37:02.959
- Are we sure?

37:03.003 --> 37:05.658
- No doubt.

37:05.701 --> 37:07.529
- Cop that was with him
was Parnell.

37:07.573 --> 37:09.618
Still don't know
who the third dude was.

37:09.662 --> 37:12.578
- It doesn't matter.

37:12.621 --> 37:13.840
If he's rolling
with the Brotherhood,

37:13.883 --> 37:15.537
he gets what they get.

37:16.712 --> 37:18.018
All right, find them,

37:18.061 --> 37:21.369
strike back,
make sure they know it was us.

37:21.413 --> 37:23.850
♪

37:23.893 --> 37:27.027
[soft jazz music playing]

37:27.070 --> 37:33.990
♪

37:35.557 --> 37:38.299
- Excuse me.

37:38.343 --> 37:40.258
- Mrs. Webb.

37:40.301 --> 37:41.868
- Mr. Webb.

37:41.911 --> 37:43.696
- May I have this dance?

37:43.739 --> 37:45.219
- Why, yes.

37:45.263 --> 37:49.005
- ♪ Oh, what
a lovely time it was ♪

37:49.049 --> 37:52.357
♪ How sublime it was too

37:52.400 --> 37:54.489
♪ I

37:54.533 --> 37:57.144
[keys jingling]

37:57.187 --> 38:00.060
- Come on, Smoke.

38:00.103 --> 38:01.888
- Hey, I got an extra
thousand for y'all

38:01.931 --> 38:03.498
if I'm at the helipad by 10:00.

38:03.542 --> 38:04.760
- Gimme that.

38:04.804 --> 38:07.023
Flashing it around.

38:07.067 --> 38:10.505
- ♪ I'll say it was grand

38:10.549 --> 38:14.466
♪ Grand to be alive

38:14.509 --> 38:15.554
- Yeah.
- Whoa!

38:15.597 --> 38:17.251
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.
- Yeah.

38:17.295 --> 38:19.862
You might wanna roll me
those jewels, Donnelly.

38:19.906 --> 38:21.560
Now.
- Hugo.

38:21.603 --> 38:22.952
You're making
a big mistake here.

38:22.996 --> 38:24.519
You don't have to do this.
- Shut up.

38:24.563 --> 38:26.391
- I said now.

38:26.434 --> 38:28.697
- ♪ I'm all yours

38:28.741 --> 38:33.267
♪ I did not know

38:33.311 --> 38:35.400
- Just be cool,
let's give them what they want.

38:35.443 --> 38:38.098
- Relax.

38:38.141 --> 38:39.752
- [grunts]
There you go.

38:39.795 --> 38:41.580
It's all yours, it's all yours.

38:41.623 --> 38:42.885
- Hey!

38:44.060 --> 38:46.367
- Drop the case,
drop the case!

38:46.411 --> 38:48.761
Get your ass over there.
- Get over to your friend.

38:48.804 --> 38:50.328
Faster,
get over to your friend.

38:50.371 --> 38:51.938
He told you it was a bad idea,
didn't he?

38:51.981 --> 38:53.548
Drop that gun, drop the gun.

38:53.592 --> 38:55.463
Get away--get to the hospital.

38:55.507 --> 38:58.292
- ♪ I wanted love
in paradise ♪

38:58.336 --> 39:00.773
[engine revving]

39:00.816 --> 39:04.385
[tense music]

39:04.429 --> 39:07.345
[applause]

39:21.054 --> 39:22.403
- [sighs]

39:27.321 --> 39:28.627
- You all right?
- I don't like guns

39:28.670 --> 39:31.194
being shoved in my face.

39:31.238 --> 39:34.284
- Yeah, I picked up
on that vibe, brother.

39:36.852 --> 39:39.942
[chuckling]

39:42.684 --> 39:44.469
- You gotta learn to duck.

39:44.512 --> 39:48.603
[both laughing]

39:48.647 --> 39:50.039
- Unbelievable.

39:52.433 --> 39:53.826
You did good, Stabler.

39:55.697 --> 39:57.177
Very good.

40:00.049 --> 40:01.399
Glad I had you along.

40:04.227 --> 40:07.013
Saved my ass.

40:07.056 --> 40:09.668
And my nose, probably.
- Yeah.

40:09.711 --> 40:13.498
[unsettling music]

40:13.541 --> 40:15.064
- I think you might be ready.

40:20.418 --> 40:21.723
- Ready?

40:26.380 --> 40:27.381
- Come on.

40:36.085 --> 40:37.260
Come on.

40:37.304 --> 40:44.267
♪

41:23.611 --> 41:26.571
[dramatic music]

41:26.614 --> 41:33.534
♪

41:53.641 --> 41:56.818
[wolf howls]
